                                <span class="text-gray-500">+</span>
                            </button>
                            <div id="section4" class="mt-2 hidden">
                                <p class="text-gray-700">Fraud prevention remains one of the best investments a firm can
                                    make. Having responded to a myriad of allegations over our collective careers, CRA’s
                                    forensic accountants bring a methodical and well-informed approach to the design,
                                    communication, and implementation of an enhanced fraud and compliance framework. Any
                                    compliance program is susceptible to fraud or corruption risks, and therefore,
                                    properly timed and executed assessments can test the effectiveness of even the most
                                    well-intentioned programs. Whether performing risk assessments, evolving compliance
                                    systems, measuring progress, or simply educating the organization, CRA tailors
                                    compliance and fraud risk management procedures to align with the priorities of our
                                    clients.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="colo-2">
                        <div class="border-b py-6">
                            <button
                                class="flex justify-between items-center w-full text-left text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-600"
                                onclick="toggleSection('section5')">
                                Inability to Pay Analysis
                                <span class="text-gray-500">+</span>
                            </button>
                            <div id="section5" class="mt-2 hidden">
                                <p class="text-gray-700">CRA assists clients that are faced with potentially
                                    catastrophic government-imposed fines by independently assessing and credibly
                                    communicating our opinions as to their ability or inability to pay. We leverage our
                                    deep accounting, finance, and economic skills to analyze and quantify the impact
                                    that a fine will have on the organization; on the marketplace, workforce, and other
                                    stakeholders; and on the organization’s ability to subsequently comply with other
                                    laws and regulations. We consider guidance, where appropriate, from the government
                                    agencies themselves, and from our sources such as the FASB, PCAOB, AICPA, IRS,
                                    Bankruptcy Code, and case law.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-b py-6">
                            <button
                                class="flex justify-between items-center w-full text-left text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-600"
