                                Model Error Investigations
                                <span class="text-gray-500">+</span>
                            </button>
                            <div id="section6" class="mt-2 hidden">
                                <p class="text-gray-700">Businesses frequently rely upon models to support investment
                                    decisions, ensure accurate financial reporting, perform customer transaction
                                    monitoring, engage in capital stress testing, and more. Numerous regulators in the
                                    US and UK have engaged in enforcement actions against companies who have used and
                                    relied upon models, but which were later discovered to have had errors, inadequate
                                    controls, poor governance, and/or been used in ways other than intended. Model
                                    errors often lead to fines, monitors, litigation, and other sanctions. Our team
                                    helps clients investigate allegations of model errors, enhance model governance, and
                                    defend against litigation and regulatory scrutiny.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

